entries.femaleVariant: Good morning, V.
Hey, Del.
[Get in] Take me to the Afterlife.
Hang on.
Hang on. Need a minute.
My, don't you look tired. Did you have a difficult night?
Difficult few weeks.
Ey, boss.
Hey. He there yet?
No' yet. He'll be on time, though.
And the gear?
Here we are. Shall I await your return?
No, thanks, Del. I'll be all right.
Best of luck, V. May your plans bear succulent fruit!
All set with the heat. Rest, too – full tank, ready to launch.
The Afterlife, head over there.
Are you prepared for takeoff?
Can I help? I'd very much like to help you.
Any news about Arasaka? What's the latest in town?
Too late to help.
Just take me to the Afterlife. Without the talking.
Mood in the city – what's it like?
And the street?
Rumors abound that you've taken on something rather big. And that one with great power and even greater funds is backing you.
Good to know.
Honestly? It's too late. I can't be helped.
entries.maleVariant: Honestly, heh? It's too late. I can't be helped.

entries.femaleVariant: You've unlimited resources at your disposal after your raid on Mikoshi. All at the Afterlife eat out of your hand. I'm certain…
Don't worry about it.
If you say so.
Just take me to the Afterlife. Quick, no more chatter. Gotta focus.
Naturally, I've selected the shortest route. We'll be there shortly.
One last thing before I shut up as requested – don't worry, V.
May I ask you something, V?
Shoot.
You mentioned recently that only one thing matters to you – to gaze upon Night City from the very top.
I hope your deep learning covered metaphor – and you're not about to tell me to exercise caution when looking out the window.
Sarcasm. Funny.
No. I wished to ask what will come next? Once you've achieved your aim?
Fulfillment?
I'll die.
Ask me then.
I'll feel fulfilled.
Truly?
Sure fuckin' hope so.
Then I'll die.
While I understand your meaning, I can't seem to imagine that.
Might be I'm beyond help, anybody's. But that's OK.
It's more than OK.
Ask me once it's done, once it's all over.
Of course. I shall be sure to do so.
We will be traveling along restricted air corridors.
No delays anticipated.
Preem.
We have arrived at your destination.
Thank you for choosing the Delamain service. Have a nice day.
Hello. Thank you for choosing the Delamain service.
Where shall we fly today?
If I may deign, you look frightfully fatigued. Was it a difficult night?
Difficult few weeks.
I'm truly sorry to hear that.
Just get me to the Afterlife, stat.
Little too late for medical help.
As to any medical aid, a day late and an eddy short for that.
I'm afraid I don't understand. You've practically unlimited resources at your disposal. I'm certain we can find an appropriate solution.
Don't worry about it, Del.
As you wish.
Get me to the Afterlife. And floor it.
Naturally.
Nothing much besides. Arasaka is in chaos, striving to restore even a semblance of order. It seems you, the Afterlife, are safe... for now.
If anyone can pull this particular job off, it's you. See, I know you a bit, and…
Well, I'm quite sure you know what I mean.
Thanks, Del. I do.
If there's anything I can do to help you avoid that fate, please do tell me.
And I am glad.
Why's that?
That I'll be able to ask. That means it'll work. You will, in fact, return.
Mhm...
His people came to scan the place earlier. Check, make sure everything's clean before he arrived.
Thanks. Be there soon.
I've chosen the optimal route. We'll be arriving shortly.
The Delamain network is pleased to offer complementary services that may just be the ideal remedy for your current condition.
What's more, I'm delighted to inform you that Delamain has joined forces with Trauma Team.
With our limited-time only "Safe Travels" package, you have a full range of medical services available to you at your fingertips.
Heh, thought we didn't notice 'em.
Please sit back, relax and enjoy the stunning views of our fine city.
Could be the last time I do.
Mhm. Thanks.
Hm, might be the last time I get a look at this place.
Mhm. Thanks.
Judging by my clients' reviews, the city is "truly breathtaking."
Mh, no doubt.
Do you plan to leave Night City?
One way or another.
In that case, I wish you a swift return home.
They also call it "a metropolis of near paralyzing beauty."
Don't doubt it.
"It's a knockout."
Sure is.
"Poised to enchant you with promises of a better tomorrow."
You don't say...
This city, as certain of my clients note, is "a true West Coast gem."
Uh-huh.
Here we are.
Have a nice day, V!
Your wish is my command.
As you wish.
Good morning, V.
Where shall we zip off to today?
Absolutely.
Naturally, V.
Of course.
Yes, of course.
We'll be taking those special air corridors. Excited as I am?
So we should make good time.
Awesome.
My, you look knackered. Hard night?
Difficult few weeks.
Golly, I'm sorry to hear that. Your incursion into Arasaka Tower has given you all – respect, unlimited resources. Now, for physical ailments…
If it helps, I can offer additional services and spa treatments and whatnot. That may be just the thing for your current condition.
In fact, I've teamed up with Trauma Team to provide a medical care package. Limited time offer, "Safe Travels" I call it – you could try it now.
Get me to the Afterlife, stat.
Little too late for medical help.
As to any medical aid, a day late and an eddy short for that.
I'm afraid I don't understand. But you've unlimited resources at your disposal, I'm certain we can find something appropriate and thoroughly satisfying.
Don't worry about it.
Have it your way.
Just take me to the Afterlife. And floor it.
Absolutely.
I've chosen the optimal route. We'll be arriving shortly.
Please sit back, relax and enjoy the stunning views of our fine city.
Could be the last time I do.
Mhm. Thanks.
Hm, might be the last time I get a look at this place.
Are you going somewhere, for good?
One way or another.
In that case, I'll hope to see you again soon!
Night City, as my clients note, is "a true West Coast gem."
Uh-huh.
They also call it "a metropolis of near paralyzing beauty."
Don't doubt it.
Mhm. Thanks.
If you care to believe my customers, the city is "truly breathtaking."
Mh, no doubt.
"It's a knockout."
Sure is.
"Poised to enchant you with promises of a better tomorrow."
You don't say...
What do you say?
[Get out]
Success weighing you down – is that it? I was under the impression you had gotten all you wanted, that you'd shown the city exactly who is top dog.
Arasaka's problems continue to compound – organizational disintegration, its share price has collapsed, public mistrust is at an all-time high… I could go on.
"Secure Your Soul" was to be a smashing success for Arasaka. It turned into a horrific curse. They lost all resources related to the program.
What's going on with Arasaka? And how's the sich in the city?
Here's an item that might interest you – the Arasaka crisis continues, the corporation still teeters.
Any news about Arasaka?
Aggregated media mentions indicate a positively mammoth stain on the corporation's image, as well as financial and political defeat.
Any news about Arasaka?
How's the sich in the city?
Arasaka's in a right pickle – an organizational shambles, its share price has tanked, public mistrust is at an all-time high… I could go on.
"Secure Your Soul" was to be a mammoth success for Arasaka. It turned into a mammoth curse. They lost all resources related to the program.
And the street? What's the street sayin'?
Rumors abound, naturally. You're onto something huge with someone even huger backing you, their resources yet more huge.
Nothing much besides. Arasaka's a mess, trying to rein in the chaos. At any rate, you, the Afterlife, you're safe... for some time anyway.
Preem, just preem.
Mhm, promised the rich immortality, sold them on it. Actually collected engrams and knowledge. A bid for control, for power, I say.
Mhm, promised the rich immortality, sold them on it. Actually collected engrams and knowledge. A bid for control, for power, I say.
Precisely. In any event, it will be some time before Arasaka successfully reorganizes. It seems you, the Afterlife, are safe... for now.
